President Barack Obama issued a statement on the "Day of Portugal, Camões, and the Portuguese Communities," expressing the strong and longstanding friendship between the United States and Portugal. The day commemorates the passing of Luís Vaz de Camões, Portugal's greatest poet, known for his epic poem, Os Lusíadas, which celebrates the golden age of Portuguese exploration and discovery. President Obama acknowledged the contributions of Portuguese-Americans and extended his best wishes to those celebrating Portuguese culture and heritage.